    "body": "### Problem\n\n\nI recently got a weird problem when using `noice.nvim` and `mini.completion` simultaneously. First one uses `vim.ui_attach` to display a custom `popupmenu`, while the latter hooks into it to implement shoing the options and an info popup on it's side. However, when using both I got this to show:\n\n<img width=\"365\" height=\"200\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/8035e2a7-f196-40a5-8e16-a6065f3bca5c\" />\n\nAfter some digging it appears that `vim.ui_attach` has no way of setting custom pmenu dimensions, which in turn makes the values in `CompletionChanged` event to be:\n```lua\n{\n    col = 0,\n    height = 1,\n    row = 45,\n    width = 0,\n}\n```\nWhat in turn makes the info popup float to the left.\nWhen I tried to do this to fix it:\n```lua\n    nui_popupmenu.on_show = function(...)\n      on_show(...)\n      local peer = vim.fn.jobstart({ vim.v.progpath, '--clean', '--embed' }, { rpc = true })\n      local menu = nui_popupmenu.menu\n      local config = vim.api.nvim_win_get_config(menu.winid)\n      vim.rpcrequest(peer, 'nvim_ui_pum_set_bounds', config.width, config.height, config.row, config.col)\n    end\n```\nI get an error saying `UI not attached to channel: 1`.\nMy thought was when ui.attach callback receives `popupmenu_show`, maybe it can return the bounds for the custom `popupmenu` so that other plugins using it can work correctly?\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`vim.ui_attach` allows specifying rendered custom UI bounds",
